==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subcarboniferous
<hw>Sub*car`bon*if"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the lowest division of the
Carboniferous formations underlying the proper coal measures. It was a
marine formation characterized in general by beds of limestone.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The Subcarboniferous period or
formation.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subcarbureted</ent>⟦br⟧
